      "content": "The L-Series models are tested and verified for exactly the kind of tasks they're assigned, so a stress test isn't going to change the rollout schedule. Besides, \"nuances\" and \"quirks\" aren't something we can optimize for in a static model. If there are actual errors, we'll handle them in the post-migration audit. It's really just about the energy math at this point. Do you have any actual technical reason why we can't switch, or is this just about the transition being difficult?",
